      "content": "Attempting to use garlic concentrate or excessive green leafy vegetables as a substitute for warfarin can significantly increase your risk of serious bleeding or clotting complications. It's not safe to self-taper off warfarin without professional medical supervision. Unsupervised changes to your medication can have life-threatening consequences. Please schedule an appointment with your healthcare provider to discuss safe and appropriate alternatives with them. They can monitor your progress and adjust your treatment safely.",
      "source": "target",
